This project includes work originally developed as part of the
Unbound Force project (https://github.com/unbound-force/unbound-force),
specifically the review-council command at:
  internal/scaffold/assets/opencode/commands/review-council.md

The original copyright is retained per Apache License 2.0, Section 4(c).

Changes from the original Unbound Force implementation:

  - Restructured from a monolithic command file (~283 lines) into a
    hybrid SKILL.md state machine with bash scripts and LLM phase files
  - Split each reviewer agent into separate -code.md and -spec.md
    variants for mode-specific reviews
  - Extracted shared procedures (evidence discipline, pack loading,
    output format, self-attestation) into reviewer-protocol.md
  - Replaced hardcoded Unbound Force tool references (Gaze, Dewey,
    Speckit/OpenSpec) with configurable extension points
  - Generalized mode detection from UF-specific branch patterns
    (NNN-*, opsx/*) to a file-path heuristic
  - Added superpowers spec directory (docs/superpowers/) as a
    recognized spec artifact location
  - Reorganized convention packs: renamed default.md to base.md,
    removed -custom.md companions in favor of priority-based overrides
